<TITLE> Murshid Kuli Khan deputy BB governor </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 12 (bdnews24.com)  Bangladesh Bank executive director Murshid Kuli Khan has been appointed deputy governor on a four-year contract to the central bank as part of an administrative reshuffle, the establishment ministry said in a statement Monday. Joint commissioner (imports) of Chittagong Customs House Ashraf Ali Faruque has been deputed as a deputy director to the Anticorruption Commission. ACC deputy director Jiban Krishna Roy, who had been on deputation at the antigraft watchdog, has been transferred to Bangladesh Bank, his previous work place. Army officer Major Julfiker Haider has been appointed survey superintendent on deputation. Several shuffles have also been made in some deputy-secretary level positions. Officers on special duty such as Jyotirmoy Barman and Wahidul Islam of the establishment ministry have been attached to the Board of Investment to assist the Regulatory Reforms Commission. Deputy secretary of the shipping ministry Akhteruzzaman Hamidi has been transferred to the water resources ministry, deputy secretary of the water resources ministry Abdul Halim to the shipping ministry and deputy secretary of the housing and public works ministry Mojibur Rahman to Jatiya Sangsad Secretariat. Deputy secretary Jagannath Das Khokan, who was an OSD, has been transferred to the post and telecommunications ministry. bdnew
